Our results show the influence of a similar causality discourse around a higher Twitter engagement around COP-23 (N4 (2017–2020)). This COP had a specific agenda called ’Human Settlement Day’, which focused on cities, affordable housing and climate action. Such topical shifts also cause greater engagement within the users-generated network, as seen through increases in retweets, following, and followers count during N4 (shown in SI Figures A9, A10 and A11). Furthermore, with a similar causality lens, we found the tweet volume grew exponentially with the launch of the IPCC Special Report on Global Warming of 1.5 ∘\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
